cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about single image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new network architecture that uses feature modulation to capture more informative features and maintain long-term information. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to deep learning and neural networks. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
